[Student "W"]
{[showcards S:ST]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \H4, West plays the \HJ, won by North with \HA.

North plays the \SJ, you follow with \S5, dummy \S3 and West plays the \S2. North continues with the \ST 

Play the \S6.

West's \S2 tells you he had an ODD number of \Ss, obviously 3. Since North also must have 3, you must take your \SA on the third round, depriving dummy of the extra \S trick.

North may now turn to the \D suit, but your side can win the first \D and drive out North's \HK. You will win 2 \Hs, 2 \Ds and the \SA, down 1}
[Play "W"]H4

